<seg id=1> Cease-Fire Announce By IRA </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> London, August 31, (Xinhua News Agency)  The Irish Republic Army (IRA) announced today that from midnight today, the IRA will stop all military actions and implement an "unconditional cease-fire for an infinite period". </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In the statement released by the IRA to the British and Irish press, it said that the decision was made because of the present situation and for the progress of the North Ireland Peace Process, and it had been passed to all levels of its military strength. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The statement called on the British government to face straight its responsibility and urged all parties to deal with new situation to be brought about by the cease-fire with determination and patience. It also called for a broad-based negotiation attended by the British and Irish governments and all the major parties in North Ireland to solve the North Ireland problems. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The statement said that the cease-fire of the IRA provided a chance for a "fair and forever solution"of the North Ireland problem. </seg>
<seg id=6> It also reiterated that the IRA did not give up its republic goal, i.e. the unification of the whole island of Ireland. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> To achieve the unification of North Ireland and the republic of Ireland, the IRA had been committed to a 25-year long violence. </seg>
</p>
